	abstract = {We have explored different methods of improving the accuracy of a Naive Bayes classifier for sentiment analysis. We observed that a combination of methods like effective negation handling, word n-grams and feature selection by mutual information results in a significant improvement in accuracy. This implies that a highly accurate and fast sentiment classifier can be built using a simple Naive Bayes model that has linear training and testing time complexities. We achieved an accuracy of 88.80% on the popular IMDB movie reviews dataset. The proposed method can be generalized to a number of text categorization problems for improving speed and accuracy. © 2013 Springer-Verlag.},
	type = {Conference paper},
	publication_stage = {Final},
